Basic date/time networking assignment.
To be run from command line.

Server needs 3 port numbers as parameters.
The ports are for requests in English, Maori and German respectively.
Each port must be unique and between 1024 and 64000 (inclusive)

Client needs request type, server ip and port as parameters.
Request type is either "date" or "time"
server ip is the IPv4 address of the machine the server is being run on.
the port is the port to connect to on the server.

The client will send the server a UDP "request packet", if this is receieved
the server will build up a response and send it back. The response will
contain the current date/time info as integers and in a text format.
